%20India%20and%20Nepal%20to%20occasionally%20experience%20moderate%20earthquakes%20due%20to%20fluctuations%20in%20seismic%20activity%20as%20the%20region%20is%20situated%20near%20active%20faults%2C%20Union%20Earth%20Sciences%20Minister%20Kiren%20Rijiju%20said%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20written%20reply%20to%20a%20question%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20Rijiju%20said%20the%20activation%20of%20the%20Almora%20fault%20in%20western%20Nepal%20was%20the%20reason%20for%20earthquakes%20in%20parts%20of%20north%20India%20and%20Nepal%2C%20which%20led%20to%20a%205.8%20magnitude%20quake%20on%20January%2024%20and%206.2%20and%206.4%20magnitude%20temblors%20on%20October%203%20and%20November%203%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20mainshocks%2C%20accompanied%20by%20subsequent%20aftershocks%2C%20led%20to%20an%20increased%20frequency%20of%20earthquakes%20in%202023%2C%20Rijiju%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20background%20seismicity%20remained%20unchanged%20during%20this%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20minister%20said%20northern%20India%20and%20Nepal%20experienced%2097%20earthquakes%20of%20magnitude%203.0%20to%203.9%20from%20January%20to%20November%20against%2041%20quakes%20each%20in%202022%20and%202021%20and%2042%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20region%20experienced%2021%20earthquakes%20of%20magnitude%204.0-4.9%20from%20January-November%20against%2020%20in%202022%20and%2018%20each%20in%202021%20and%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20common%20for%20northern%20India%20and%20Nepal%20to%20occasionally%20experience%20moderate%20earthquakes%2C%20and%20fluctuations%20in%20seismic%20activity.%20Nepal%20and%20the%20neighbouring%20northern%20part%20of%20India%2C%20situated%20near%20the%20active%20faults%20of%20the%20Himalayan%20region%2C%20are%20highly%20seismically%20active%20areas%20prone%20to%20frequent%20earthquakes%20due%20to%20collision%20tectonics%2C%20where%20the%20Indian%20plate%20subducts%20beneath%20the%20Eurasian%20Plate%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Almora%20fault%20is%20a%20high-angle%20west-northwest-east-southeast%20to%20northwest-southeast%20trending%20tectonic%20plane%20that%20separates%20the%20Garhwal%20group%20of%20inner%20lesser%20Himalayas%20in%20the%20north%20from%20the%20Jaunsar%20and%20Dudatoli%20groups%20of%20outer%20lesser%20Himalayas%20in%20the%20south.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERijiju%20said%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Indian%20Standards%20(BIS)%20has%20published%20the%20Seismic%20Zoning%20Map%20of%20India%2C%20ranging%20from%20Zone%20II%20to%20V%20and%20offers%20guidelines%20for%20implementing%20the%20essential%20engineering%20codes%20and%20practices%20to%20construct%20earthquake-resistant%20buildings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Disaster%20Management%20Authority%20has%20been%20the%20agency%20responsible%20for%20various%20precautionary%20measures%20such%20as%20earthquake%20drills%2C%20awareness%20programmes%2C%20earthquake%20management%20to%20enhance%20preparedness%20and%20response%20to%20earthquake%20related%20incidents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%2024%2C%20an%20earthquake%20of%20magnitude%205.8%20hit%20Nepal.%20It%20was%20strongly%20felt%20in%20Delhi%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Uttarakhand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20October%203%2C%20two%20earthquakes%20of%20magnitude%204.6%20and%206.2%20jolted%20Nepal%20and%20the%20tremors%20were%20felt%20in%20Delhi-NCR.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%203%2C%20a%20powerful%20earthquake%20of%206.4%20magnitude%20hit%20Nepal%20with%20more%20than%20382%20aftershocks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701925200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Fia9ce6j_earthquakes-strike-nepal_625x300_03_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fearthquake-2023-india