D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657144960ec98e92f74d01cc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWild%20horses%20are%20called%20brumbies%20in%20Australia%2C%20and%20can%20often%20be%20seen%20as%20pests.%3Cp%3EFairfax%20Media%20via%20Getty%20Images%2FFairfax%20Media%20via%20Getty%20Images%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOfficials%20in%20New%20South%20Wales%20say%20they've%20authorized%20the%20shooting%20of%20wild%20horses%20from%20helicopters.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey've%20been%20given%20a%20task%20of%20eliminating%20some%2014%2C000%20wild%20horses%20at%20a%20national%20park%20in%20four%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOfficials%20now%20say%20they'll%20never%20meet%20their%20goal%20if%20they%20don't%20introduce%20aerial%20shootings.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20New%20South%20Wales%20government%20has%20authorized%20an%20%26quot%3Baerial%20shooting%26quot%3B%20program%20to%20cull%20a%20population%20of%20wild%20horses%20at%20one%20of%20its%20largest%20national%20parks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20culling%20method%20has%20been%20adopted%20as%20part%20of%20a%20state%20mandate%20to%20reduce%20an%20estimated%2017%2C000%20wild%20horses%20in%20Kosciuszko%20National%20Park%20to%20just%203%2C000%20by%202027%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.environment.nsw.gov.au%2Fnews%2Fwild-horse-management-in-kosciuszko-national-park%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eofficials%20said%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAerial%20shooting%26quot%3B%20would%20involve%20operatives%20firing%20on%20the%20horses%20from%20helicopters%20%E2%80%94%20a%20tactic%20that%20the%20local%20government%20trialed%20in%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20trial%2C%20officials%20shot%20270%20horses%20over%20two%20days%20while%20veterinarians%20accompanied%20them%20in%20the%20helicopters%20to%20observe%2C%20the%20New%20South%20Wales%20government%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOfficials%20said%20the%20veterinarians%20also%20inspected%2043%20of%20the%20horses%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20and%20found%20that%20%26quot%3Bthere%20were%20no%20adverse%20animal%20welfare%20events.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20median%20time%20from%20shooting%20to%20insensibility%20was%205%20seconds%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said.%20%26quot%3BNo%20horses%20were%20non-fatally%20wounded%26quot%3B.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20average%20of%207.5%20shots%20were%20used%20to%20kill%20each%20horse%2C%20officials%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20trial%20over%2C%20the%20government%20said%20it's%20moving%20fully%20ahead%20with%20the%20helicopter%20shootings%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20would%20%26quot%3Bnot%20be%20possible%26quot%3B%20to%20meet%20the%202027%20deadline%20without%20the%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurrent%20government%20estimates%20of%20the%20national%20park's%20wild%20horse%20population%20sit%20between%2012%2C934%20and%2022%2C546%20horses%2C%20with%20a%20best%20gauge%20of%20around%2017%2C400.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20the%20government%20wants%20to%20cull%20horses%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20horses%2C%20which%20are%20referred%20to%20as%20feral%20horses%20or%20brumbies%20by%20Australians%2C%20are%20descended%20from%20escaped%20or%20lost%20horses%20brought%20to%20the%20continent%20by%20European%20settlers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finvasives.org.au%2Four-work%2Fferal-animals%2Fferal-horses%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoften%20seen%20as%20pests%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20can%20destroy%20local%20environments%20by%20compacting%20and%20eroding%20soil%2C%20defecating%20in%20water%20sources%2C%20and%20chewing%20on%20trees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224765%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Brumbies%20in%20the%20wild%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657146b67a3c8094d5da813f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223177%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBrumbies%20are%20the%20descendants%20of%20horses%20brought%20by%20European%20settlers.%3Cp%3EBrook%20Mitchell%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20their%20populations%20grow%20too%20large%2C%20they%20start%20overfeeding%20on%20vegetation%2C%20which%20can%20disrupt%20ecosystems%20and%20endanger%20native%20animal%20species.%20The%20horses%20can%20also%20threaten%20crops%20or%20interfere%20with%20farming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20New%20South%20Wales%20government%20originally%20tried%20containing%20the%20horse%20population%20through%20aerial%20shootings%20in%202000%2C%20but%20stopped%20after%20being%20met%20with%20public%20outcry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20however%2C%20the%20horse%20population%20in%20Australia%20has%20surged%20so%20high%20that%20the%20government's%20scientific%20committee%20warned%20in%20May%20they%20could%20be%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Faustralia-news%2F2023%2Fmay%2F08%2Fferal-horses-an-imminent-threat-that-could-cause-extinction-of-several-endangered-australian-species-inquiry-warned%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bcrucial%20factor%20that%20causes%20the%20final%20extinction%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20six%20critically%20endangered%20animals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESupporters%20of%20protecting%20the%20wild%20horses%20say%20the%20animals%20are%20part%20of%20Australia's%20heritage%2C%20and%20have%20decried%20the%20revival%20of%20the%20aerial%20shootings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20charity%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.savethebrumbies.org%2Fnews%2Fspeak-up-for-brumbies%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESave%20the%20Brumbies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20example%2C%20has%20accused%20the%20government%20of%20assessing%20the%20horse%20population%20through%20%26quot%3Bflawed%20survey%20methodology%26quot%3B%20and%20is%20urging%20for%20a%20recount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJan%20Carter%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20charity%2C%20wrote%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aph.gov.au%2FParliamentary_Business%2FCommittees%2FSenate%2FEnvironment_and_Communications%2FFeralHorses47%2FSubmissions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubmission%20to%20the%20Australian%20parliament%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20August%20saying%20the%20government%20should%20focus%20investing%20in%20efforts%20to%20re-home%20the%20animals%20or%20fertility%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20Heritage%20Brumbies%20are%20a%20national%20icon%20and%20part%20of%20our%20history%2C%26quot%3B%20Carter%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThey%20deserve%20recognition%2C%20not%20bullets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETensions%20over%20horse%20cullings%20have%20even%20resulted%20in%20threats%20against%20government%20officials.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2022%2Fsep%2F30%2Fpolice-investigate-threat-to-firebomb-national-parks-office-over-kosciuszko-horse-cull%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%20September%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20Kosciuszko%20National%20Park%20office%20received%20a%20letter%20saying%20someone%20wanted%20to%20%26quot%3Bfirebomb%26quot%3B%20the%20location%2C%20police%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faustralia-shoot-wild-horses-brumbies-helicopter-new-south-wales-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701923158000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6571451c0ec98e92f74d01f3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faustralia-shoot-wild-horses-brumbies-helicopter-new-south-wales-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20New%20South%20Wales%20government%20said%20it's%20going%20full%20steam%20ahead%20with%20its%20program%20to%20shoot%20wild%20horses%2C%20which%20are%20often%20seen%20as%20pests%20in%20Australia.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mloh%40businessinsider.com%20(Matthew%20Loh)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A27%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faustralia-shoot-wild-horses-brumbies-helicopter-new-south-wales-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Karnataka%20CM%20Seeks%20Clarification%20on%20Rs%20798.03%20Crore%20IGST%20Deduction%3B%20Revenue%20Minister%20Raises%20Alarm%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F18164526%2FFwBN2HcakAEGvBw.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EKarnataka%20chief%20minister%20Siddaramaiah%20has%20expressed%20apprehensions%20over%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi-led%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20move%20to%20impose%20sanctions%20on%20states%E2%80%99%20share%20of%20the%20Integrated%20Goods%20and%20Services%20Tax%20(IGST).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESiddaramaiah%20has%20penned%20a%20letter%20to%20Union%20minister%20for%20finance%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20seeking%20clarification%20on%20the%20deduction%20of%20Rs%20798.03%20crore%20from%20Karnataka%E2%80%99s%20IGST%20share.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20is%20said%20to%20have%20highlighted%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20concerns%20regarding%20the%20accumulation%20of%20substantial%20negative%20balances%2C%20amounting%20to%20Rs%2034%2C000%20crore%2C%20and%20requested%20transparency%20on%20the%20methodology%20employed%20for%20distributing%20this%20negative%20balance%20among%20the%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Siddaramaiah%20expressed%20the%20pressing%20need%20for%20a%20phased-deduction%20approach%2C%20proposing%2010%20instalments%20to%20alleviate%20the%20immediate%20impact%20on%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20exclusive%20conversation%20with%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESouth%20First%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Karnataka%20revenue%20minister%20Krishna%20Byre%20Gowda%20criticised%20the%20Union%20government%20for%20deducting%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20IGST%20significantly%20without%20giving%20any%20prior%20intimation%20or%20notice%20on%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20after%20reports%20emerged%20indicating%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20planned%20to%20deduct%20Rs%20332%20crore%20from%20Kerala%E2%80%99s%20IGST%20settlement%20for%20November%2C%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20finance%20minister%20K.N.%20Balagopal%20penned%20a%20letter%20to%20Sitharaman%20appealing%20to%20revoke%20its%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESiddaramaiah%E2%80%99s%20letter%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESiddaramaiah%2C%20in%20his%20letter%20to%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20conveyed%20his%20apprehensions%20and%20sought%20clarifications%20concerning%20the%20recent%20provisional%20settlement%20of%20IGST%20for%20the%20return%20filing%20month%20of%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20letter%20directed%20to%20Sitharaman%20dated%20December%201%2C%20he%20expressed%20his%20concerns%20regarding%20the%20adjustment%20of%20Rs%20798.03%20crore%20from%20the%20IGST%20settlement%2C%20labelled%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9CAdjustment%20of%20Advance%20Apportionment%20to%20make%20up%20a%20shortfall%20in%20IGST%20balance%20as%20of%2026%20December%2C%202022%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAcknowledging%20the%20complexities%20inherent%20in%20financial%20matters%2C%20Karnataka%20was%20keen%20to%20gain%20detailed%20insights%20into%20critical%20aspects%2C%20said%20Siddaramaiah.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20chief%20minister%2C%20however%2C%20questioned%20the%20rationale%20behind%20allowing%20the%20accumulation%20of%20substantial%20IGST%20negative%20balances%2C%20amounting%20to%20Rs%2034%2C000%20crore%2C%20emphasising%20the%20potential%20impact%20on%20state%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20foster%20better%20understanding%20and%20transparency%2C%20Karnataka%20sought%20comprehensive%20information%20on%20the%20total%20negative%20IGST%20balance%20and%20the%20methodology%20used%20for%20distributing%20this%20amount%20among%20states%20for%20recovery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20recognising%20the%20need%20for%20resources%20and%20the%20challenges%20linked%20with%20lumpsum%20deductions%2C%20the%20Karnataka%20government%20appealed%20to%20the%20Union%20government%20for%20a%20considerate%20approach%2C%20proposing%20a%20phased%20deduction%20plan%20in%2010%20instalments%20to%20alleviate%20the%20immediate%20impact%20on%20state%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmphasising%20the%20significance%20of%20a%20transparent%20and%20collaborative%20resolution%2C%20Chief%20Minister%20Siddaramaiah%20pointed%20out%3A%20%E2%80%9CAddressing%20these%20concerns%20will%20contribute%20to%20the%20effective%20functioning%20of%20the%20financial%20ecosystem.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20chief%20minister%20sought%20the%20guidance%20and%20intervention%20of%20Sitharaman%20in%20this%20matter%2C%20saying%20such%20measures%20would%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20a%20smoother%20and%20more%20sustainable%20financial%20environment%20for%20all%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20entire%20issue%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExpressing%20deep%20concerns%20over%20the%20unexpected%20deduction%20of%20%E2%82%B9798.03%20crore%20from%20Karnataka%E2%80%99s%20IGST%20settlement%2C%20Revenue%20Minister%20Krishna%20Byre%20Gowda%20raised%20significant%20issues%20with%20the%20lack%20of%20transparency%20in%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20told%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESouth%20First%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Union%20government%20has%20adjusted%20the%20IGST%20settlement%20amount%20to%20Karnataka.%20It%20claims%20that%20there%20was%20a%20shortfall%20in%20the%20IGST%20account%20which%20has%20been%20subsequently%20adjusted%20for%20all%20states.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20explanation%20on%20why%20the%20shortfall%20arose%20and%20the%20mechanism%20of%20calculation%3B%20there%20was%20no%20advanced%20notice%20either.%20If%20you%20cut%20Rs%20800%20crore%20in%20a%20month%20from%20us%2C%20we%20need%20to%20be%20prepared%20for%20this.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20exchange%20of%20information%20or%20proper%20notice%20about%20the%20sh