E%3Cp%3EThe%20suit%20also%20alleges%20that%20Davis%20told%20him%20on%20November%2011%2C%202022%20to%20shut%20down%20Salesforce%20at%20Twitter%2C%20which%20the%20company%20used%20to%20share%20information%20with%20law%20enforcement%20about%20%26quot%3Btime-sensitive%20and%20important%20legal%20matters.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERosa%20disagreed%20with%20the%20decision%2C%20and%20told%20a%20vice%20president%20of%20the%20company's%20legal%20team%20about%20his%20objections%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20alleges%20that%20Rosa%20was%20denied%20his%20promised%20severance%20package%20and%20vested%20stock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20seeks%20compensatory%2C%20emotional%20distress%2C%20and%20punitive%20damages%20from%20Musk%2C%20advisors%20such%20as%20Davis%2C%20and%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERosa's%20suit%20is%20one%20of%20several%20already%20filed%20by%20laid-off%20Twitter%20employees%20against%20Musk%20and%20X%2C%20and%20many%20say%20their%20contracts%20were%20breached%20and%20accused%20the%20billionaire%20of%20breaking%20state%20employment%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERosa%20was%20Head%20of%20Global%20Information%20Technology%20and%20Information%20Security%20when%20Musk%20assumed%20control%20of%20Twitter%2C%20and%20oversaw%20a%20team%20of%20around%20500%20staff%2C%20according%20to%20his%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20departure%20from%20the%20company%20came%20after%20Twitter's%20chief%20security%20officer%2C%20Lea%20Kissner%2C%20and%20Twitter's%20head%20of%20trust%20and%20safety%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-trust-safety-yoel-roth-fled-home-elon-musk-report-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYoel%20Roth%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20both%20left%20the%20company%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20Musk's%20takeover.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20flurry%20of%20vacancies%20prompted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fftc-tracking-elon-musk-twitter-deep-concern-privacy-execs-quit-2022-11%5C%22%20target%