20book%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3EAmerican%20Power%20and%20the%20New%20Mandarins%2C%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3ENoam%20Chomsky%20cites%20a%20news%20item%20from%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENew%20York%20Times%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eof%20March%2018%2C%201968%20captioned%20%E2%80%98Army%20Exhibit%20Bars%20Shooting%20at%20Vietnamese%20Hut%E2%80%99.%20The%20news%20item%2C%20Chomsky%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9Creports%20an%20attempt%20by%20the%20%E2%80%98peace%20movement%E2%80%99%20to%20disrupt%20an%20exhibit%20in%20the%20Chicago%20Museum%20of%20Science%20and%20Industry%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CBeginning%20today%2C%20visitors%20can%20no%20longer%20enter%20a%20helicopter%20for%20simulated%20firing%20of%20a%20machine%20gun%20at%20targets%20in%20a%20diorama%20of%20the%20Vietnam%20Central%20Highlands.%20The%20targets%20were%20a%20hut%2C%20two%20bridges%20and%20an%20ammunition%20dump%2C%20and%20a%20light%20flashed%20when%20a%20hit%20was%20scored%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20read.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CApparently%E2%80%9D%2C%20Chomsky%20continues%2C%20%E2%80%9Cit%20was%20great%20fun%20for%20the%20kiddies%20until%20those%20damned%20peaceniks%20turned%20up%20and%20started%20one%20of%20their%20interminable%20demonstrations%E2%80%A6.%20According%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETimes%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%2C%20%E2%80%98demonstrators%20particularly%20objected%20to%20children%20being%20permitted%20to%20%E2%80%98fire%E2%80%99%20at%20the%20hut%2C%20even%20though%20no%20people%20appear%20there%20or%20elsewhere%20on%20the%20diorama%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20just%20shows%20how%20unreasonable%20peaceniks%20can%20be.%20Although%20it%20is%20small%20compensation%20for%20the%20closing%20of%20this%20entertaining%20exhibit%2C%20(the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETimes%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%20adds)%2C%20%E2%80%98visitors%20can%20still%20test%20their%20skills%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20exhibition%20by%20simulated%20firing%20of%20an%20antitank%20weapon%20and%20several%20models%20of%20rifles%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20next%20paragraph%2C%20Chomsky%20goes%20on%20thus%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20can%20one%20say%20about%20a%20country%20where%20a%20museum%20of%20science%20in%20a%20great%20city%20can%20feature%20an%20exhibit%20in%20which%20people%20fire%20machine%20guns%20at%20Vietnamese%20huts%2C%20with%20a%20light%20flashing%20when%20a%20hit%20is%20scored%3F%20What%20can%20one%20say%20about%20a%20country%20where%20such%20an%20idea%20can%20even%20be%20considered%3F%20You%20have%20to%20weep%20for%20this%20country.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20was%20written%20at%20the%20height%20of%20America%E2%80%99s%20war%20on%20Vietnam%2C%20and%20Noam%20Chomsky%2C%20aged%2039%2C%20was%20already%20a%20veteran%20of%20the%20country-wide%20protests%20against%20that%20war%2C%20campaigning%20on%20university%20campuses%20including%20at%20Harvard%20and%20Berkley%2C%20leading%20an%20electrifying%20anti-war%20teach-in%20just%20outside%20the%20Pentagon%2C%20participating%20in%20civil%20disobedience%20movements%20and%20marching%20on%20Washington%20DC%20along%20with%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20others%20to%20%E2%80%98return%E2%80%99%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20(army)%20%E2%80%98draft%20cards%E2%80%99%20to%20the%20Attorney%20General%E2%80%99s%20office.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EC%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehomsky%2C%20a%20tenured%20full%20professor%20at%20MIT%20since%20he%20was%2032%2C%20had%20already%20been%20imprisoned%20several%20times%2C%20and%20was%20detained%20again%20in%20October%201967%20after%20that%20historic%20Pentagon%20demonstration.%20This%20time%2C%20he%20happened%20to%20share%20his%20prison%20cell%20with%20the%20novelist%20Norman%20Mailer%20who%2C%20in%20his%20classic%20account%20of%20this%20stirring%20moment%20in%20American%20history%20%E2%80%93%20titled%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Armies%20of%20the%20Night%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3Edescribed%20his%20cell-mate%2C%20%E2%80%9Ca%20slim%2C%20sharp-featured%20man%20with%20an%20ascetic%20expression%20and%20an%20air%20of%20gentle%20but%20absolute%20moral%20authority%E2%80%9D%2C%20seemed%20%E2%80%9Cuneasy%20at%20the%20thought%20of%20missing%20class%20on%20Monday%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20308px)%2085vw%2C%20308px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F06154752%2Funnamed.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22308%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F06154752%2Funnamed.jpg%20240w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F06154752%2Funnamed-199x300.jpg%20199w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-687956%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22463%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENormal%20Mailer%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Armies%20of%20the%20Night%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3ENew%20American%20Library%20(1968).%20The%20cover%20page%20shows%20Noam%20Chomsky%20(second%20from%20left)%20among%20other%20protesters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20an%20interview%20given%20many%20years%20later%2C%20for%20the%202006%20documentary%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3EChildren%20of%20Armageddon%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3EChomsky%20was%20asked%20if%20he%20remembered%20the%20day%20news%20of%20the%20Hiroshima%20bombing%20broke%20in%20the%20US.%20Chomsky%20replied%20%E2%80%98Yes%2C%20quite%20well%E2%80%99%2C%20whereupon%20the%20interviewer%20wanted%20to%20know%20if%20he%20recalled%20how%20he%20had%20reacted%20to%20it.%20Chomsky%20hesitated%20a%20little%20%E2%80%93%20clearly%2C%20the%20memory%20was%20still%20a%20very%20disquieting%20one%20%E2%80%93%20before%20he%20confessed%20that%20he%20had%20been%20shocked.%20%E2%80%9CDoubly%20shocked%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20added%2C%20by%20the%20sheer%20savagery%20of%20the%20act%2C%20of%20course%2C%20but%20equally%2C%20by%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccomplete%20absence%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eany%20reaction%20to%20it%E2%80%9D%20around%20him.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20aged%2016%2C%20he%20had%20just%20graduated%20from%20high%20school%20and%20was%20on%20a%20summer%20camp.%20As%20the%20news%20came%20in%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9Cit%20didn%E2%80%99t%20seem%20to%20make%20any%20difference%20to%20anybody%E2%80%A6%20and%20I%20remember%20I%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20talk%20to%20anyone.%20There%20was%20nobody.%20I%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20stay%20where%20I%20was.%20I%20just%20walked%20off%20by%20myself%20to%20somewhere%20in%20the%20woods%20and%20stayed%20there%20for%20maybe%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%E2%80%A6..%20till%20it%20was%20getting%20dark.%20%E2%80%A6I%20felt%20completely%20isolated%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChomsky%20then%20recounted%20an%20episode%20from%20several%20years%20later%2C%20possibly%20the%20early%201950s%2C%20when%20information%20about%20the%20horrors%20of%20Hiroshima%20and%20Nagasaki%20was%20still%20widely%20censored%20in%20the%20US.%20One%20evening%20in%20Boston%2C%20Chomsky%20and%20his%20wife%20felt%20like%20watching%20a%20movie.%20They%20scanned%20the%20movie%20pages%20of%20the%20local%20newspaper%20to%20decide%20which%20film%20to%20see%2C%20and%20were%20surprised%20to%20find%20a%20film%20called%20%E2%80%98Hiroshima%E2%80%99%20billed%20at%20a%20downtown%20Boston%20theatre%20located%20in%20Boston%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Redlight%E2%80%99%20district%20(so%20called%20because%20the%20neighbourhood%20mostly%20featured%20pornographic%20movies).%20The%20Chomskys%20were%20keen%20to%20check%20the%20film%20out%20and%20went.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20turned%20out%20that%20it%20was%20some%20kind%20of%20a%20poorly-made%20documentary%20film%20but%20it%20contained%20graphic%20images%20of%20the%20carnage%20of%20August%206%2C%201945%2C%20obviously%20filmed%20on-site%20at%20Hiroshima%20on%2C%20and%20immediately%20after%2C%20that%20dreadful%20day.%20There%20were%20pictures%20of%20appalling%20devastation%2C%20of%20people%20with%20their%20skin%20falling%20off%20their%20bodies%2C%20screaming%20and%20running%20towards%20the%20river%20in%20the%20hope%20of%20salving%20their%20wounds.%20And%2C%20Chomsky%20recalled%20with%20a%20perceptible%20shudder%2C%20%E2%80%9Cpeople%20in%20the%20audience%20were%20laughing%E2%80%A6%20laughing..%20They%20perhaps%20took%20it%20for%20a%20pornographic%20movie%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20One%20can%20actually%20hear%20Chomsky%E2%80%99s%20voice%20trail%20off%20as%20he%20remembers%20that%20day%20on%20camera.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChomsky%E2%80%99s%20moral%20universe%20had%20been%20shaped%2C%20by%20his%20own%20account%2C%20%E2%80%9Cby%20the%20horrors%20of%20the%201930s%2C%20by%20the%20war%20in%20Ethiopia%2C%20the%20Russian%20purges%2C%20the%20China%20incident%2C%20the%20Spanish%20Civil%20War%2C%20the%20Nazi%20atrocities%2C%20the%20Western%20reaction%20to%20these%20events%20and%2C%20in%20part%2C%20their%20complicity%20in%20them%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20The%20fall%20of%20Republican%20Barcelona%20in%20January%201939%20in%20the%20Spanish%20Civil%20War%20was%20a%20watershed%20in%20Chomsky%E2%80%99s%20intellectual%20history.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20persuaded%2010-year-old%20Noam%20to%20write%2C%20for%20his%20school%20magazine%2C%20his%20first%20published%20article.%20Even%20though%20he%20had%20taken%20up%20theoretical%20linguistics%20partly%20fortuitously%2C%20Chomsky%20was%20to%20eventually%20emerge%20as%20the%2020%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E-century%E2%80%99s%20foremost%20language%20theorist%2Fphilosopher%20whose%20work%20has%20profoundly%20influenced%20education%20theory%2C%20psychology%2C%20psycholinguistics%2C%20neurolinguistics%2C%C2%A0%20computational%20theory%20and%20computer%20learning%20as%20well%20as%20cognitive%20science%20in%20general.%20He%20pioneered%20the%20cognitivist%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20the%20then%20widely%20popular%20behaviourist%2C%20approach%20to%20language%20theory%2C%20and%20established%20its%20preeminence%20among%20the%20competing%20epistemological%20systems%20of%20human%20language.%20And%2C%20in%20a%20very%20real%20sense%2C%20Chomsky%E2%80%99s%20path-breaking%20work%20in%20language%20theory%20also%20links%20up%20with%20the%20fundamental%20moral%20concerns%20that%20have%20informed%20all%20his%20adult%20years%3A%20human%20dignity%2C%20equality%2C%20social%20justice%20and%20freedom.%20Here%E2%80%99s%20what%20he%20once%20said%20about%20the%20linkages%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F12%2F5599576288_6d200ac24c_b.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F12%2F5599576288_6d200ac24c_b.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F12%2F5599576288_6d200ac24c_b-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F12%2F5599576288_6d200ac24c_b-768x512.jpg%20768w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-88391%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENoam%20Chomsky.%20Photo%3A%20Andrew%20Rusk%2FFlickr%20CC%20BY%202.0%2C%20Marc%20Lozano%2FFlickr%20CC%20BY-SA%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20like%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20intensive%20study%20of%20one%20aspect%20of%20human%20psychology%20%E2%80%93%20human%20language%20%E2%80%93%20may%20contribute%20to%20a%20humanistic%20social%20science%20that%20will%20serve%20as%20well%20as%20an%20instrument%20for%20social%20action.%20It%20must%2C%20needless%20to%20say%2C%20be%20stressed%20that%20social%20action%20cannot%20await%20a%20firmly%20established%20theory%20of%20man%20and%20society%2C%20nor%20can%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20latter%20be%20determined%20by%20our%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehopes%20and%20moral%20judgements.%20The%20two%20%E2%80%93%20speculation%20and%20action%20%E2%80%93%20must%20progress%20as%20best%20they%20can%2C%20looking%20forward%20to%20the%20day%20when%20theoretical%20enquiry%20will%20provide%20a%20firm%20guide%20to%20the%20unending%2C%20often%20grim%2C%20but%20never%20hopeless%20struggle%20for%20freedom%20and%20social%20justice.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E(From%20the%20essay%20%3C%2Fspan%3ELanguage%20and%20Freedom%3Cb%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3Eoriginally%20a%20lecture%20given%20at%20Loyola%20University%2C%20Chicago%20in%20January%201970)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhy%20does%20Chomsky%20believe%20that%20the%20study%20of%20the%20humans%E2%80%99%20facility%20for%20language%20can%20open%20the%20door%20for%20meaningful%20social%20action%3F%20A%20clue%20to%20the%20answer%20probably%20lies%20in%20another%20part%20of%20the%20same%20essay%2C%20where%20he%20expands%20on%20the%20theme%20of%20freedom%20and%20creativity%20running%20through%20man%E2%80%99s%20use%20of%20language%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CLanguage%20is%20a%20process%20of%20free%20creation%3B%20its%20laws%20and%20principles%20are%20fixed%2C%20but%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20principles%20of%20generation%20are%20used%20is%20free%20and%20infinitely%20varied.%20Even%20the%20interpretation%20and%20use%20of%20words%20involves%20a%20process%20of%20free%20creation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFreedom%20implies%20the%20ability%20to%20make%20choices%2C%20and%20Chomsky%20never%20tires%20of%20reminding%20us%20that%20everyone%20needs%20to%20make%20a%20choice%20on%20a%20multiplicity%20of%20issues%20everyday%20if%20we%20are%20to%20stay%20human.%20In%20the%20%E2%80%98Q%26amp%3BA%E2%80%99%20session%20following%20a%20talk%20he%20delivered%20in%20the%20Asian%20School%20of%20Journalism%20in%20Chennai%20in%20October%202001%2C%20a%20budding%20journalist%20asked%20Chomsky%20if%20he%20was%20not%20being%20%E2%80%98too%20optimistic%E2%80%99%20in%20a%20world%20that%20otherwise%20looked%20quite%20bleak.%20Chomsky%E2%80%99s%20reply%20was%20simple%2C%20almost%20matter-of-fact%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20measure%20of%20how%20optimistic%20you%20ought%20to%20be.%20In%20fact%2C%20as%20far%20as%20optimism%20is%20concerned%2C%20you%20basically%20have%20two%20choices.%20You%20can%20say%2C%20%E2%80%98Nothing%20is%20going%20to%20work%20and%20so%20I%20am%20not%20going%20to%20do%20anything.%E2%80%99%20You%20can%20therefore%20guarantee%20that%20the%20worst%20possible%20outcome%20will%20come%20about.%20Or%20you%20can%20take%20the%20other%20option%20and%20say%2C%20%E2%80%98Maybe%20something%20will%20work%20and%20I%20will%20engage%20myself%20in%20trying%20to%C2%A0%20make%20it%20work.%20Maybe%20there%20is%20a%20chance%20that%20things%20will%20get%20better%E2%80%99.%20That%20is%20your%20choice.%20Nobody%20can%20tell%20you%20how%20right%20it%20is%20to%20be%20optimistic.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20329px)%2085vw%2C%20329px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F29123746%2Frequiem-for-the.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22329%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F29123746%2Frequiem-for-the.jpg%20401w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F29123746%2Frequiem-for-the-241x300.jpg%20241w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-333848%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22410%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ERequiem%20for%20the%20American%20Dream%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3ENoam%20Chomsky%3Cbr%3ESeven%20Stories%20Press%20(2017)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%20hint%20of%20high%20passion%20here%2C%20for%20Chomsky%20clearly%20thinks%20he%20is%20only%20stating%20the%20obvious.%20But%20he%20also%20knows%20that%2C%20sometimes%2C%20there%20is%20no%20such%20thing%20as%20the%20obvious%2C%20at%20any%20rate%20not%20for%20the%20modern-day%20intellectual.%20As%20far%20back%20as%20June%2C%201966%2C%20while%20delivering%20at%20Harvard%2C%20in%20an%20anti-Vietnam%20War%20rally%2C%20what%20proved%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%2020%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20century%E2%80%99s%20great%20speeches%2C%20he%20had%20said%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20the%20responsibility%20of%20intellectuals%20to%20speak%20the%20truth%20and%20to%20expose%20lies.%20This%2C%20at%20least%2C%20seems%20enough%20of%20a%20truism%20to%20pass%20without%20comment.%20Not%20so%2C%20however.%20For%20the%20modern%20intellectual%2C%20it%20is%20not%20at%20all%20obvious.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20Chomsky%2C%20however%2C%20this%20responsibility%20was%20always%20axiomatic.%20For%20the%20longest%20time%2C%20he%20has%20been%20a%20thorn%20in%20the%20side%20of%20successive%20US%20administrations%2C%20Republican%20and%20Democratic%2C%20for%20his%20incisive%2C%20insistent%20probing%20of%20the%20real%20drivers%20of%20American%20foreign%20policy.%20His%20unblinking%20gaze%20on%20how%20the%20US%20propped%20up%20the%20most%20brutal%20regimes%20in%20Nicaragua%2C%20El%20Salvadore%2C%20Guatemala%20and%20Chile%20through%20the%201970s%20earned%20him%20a%20place%20on%20President%20Nixon%E2%80%99s%20infamous%20%E2%80%98Enemies%20List%E2%80%99.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20is%20recognised%20as%20one%20of%20the%20chief%20architects%20of%20the%20independence%20of%20East%20Timor.%20By%20insistently%2C%20even%20stridently%2C%20raising%20his%20voice%20against%20unspeakable%2C%20US-aided%20Indonesian%20atrocities%20against%20the%20East%20Timorese%2C%20he%20had%20helped%20focus%20international%20public%20opinion%20on%20East%20Timor.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202002%2C%C2%A0%20he%20appeared%20unsolicited%20at%20an%20Istanbul%20court%20to%20plead%20that%20he%20be%20made%20a%20co-accused%20in%20a%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecriminal%20prosecution%20involving%20Fatih%20Tas%2C%20an%20important%20Turkish%20publisher.%20Tas%20had%20published%20a%20Turkish%20translation%20of%20Chomsky%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3EAmerican%20Interventionism%2C%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%20book%20of%20essays%20highlighting%20the%20Turkish%20government%E2%80%99s%20relentless%20persecution%20of%20Turkiye%E2%80%99s%20Kurdish%20population%20with%20American%20support.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENot%20amused%2C%20the%20Turkish%20State%20was%20prosecuting%20Tas%20for%20%E2%80%98producing%20propaganda%20against%20the%20unity%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99.%20It%20was%20dismayed%2C%20however%2C%20by%20Chomsky%E2%80%99s%20sudden%20appearance%20in%20Turkiye%20and%20his%20plea%20to%20be%20tried%20alongside%20Tas.%20All%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20media%20had%20got%20wind%20of%20the%20professor%E2%80%99s%20presence%20in%20the%20country%20and%20were%20sure%20to%20turn%20up%20in%20strength%20to%20report%20on%20the%20court%20proceedings%20live.%20The%20Turkish%20authorities%20panicked%20and%20dropped%20the%20prosecution%2C%20saving%20the%20publisher%20from%20a%20certain%20prison%20sentence.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChomsky%E2%80%99s%20reaction%20was%20characteristically%20understated.%20Because%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20US%20provides%2080%25%20of%20the%20arms%20for%20Turkiye%20for%20the%20express%20purpose%20of%20carrying%20out%20repression%E2%80%99%E2%80%99%2C%20he%20felt%20it%20was%20his%20duty%2C%20as%20a%20US%20citizen%2C%20to%20protest%20against%20Turkiye%E2%80%99s%20human%20rights%20abuses.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20many%20like%20me%20who%20have%20followed%20and%20admired%20Chomsky%E2%80%99s%20work%20for%20decades%2C%20it%20is%20unsurprising%20%E2%80%93%20because%20for%20him%20it%20is%20second%20nature%20%E2%80%93%20that%20he%20always%20downplays%20the%20impact%20of%20his%20own%20interventions%20in%20some%20of%20the%20most%20critical%20questions%20our%20world%20is%20confronted%20with%3A%20war%20and%20peace%2C%20egregious%20human%20rights%20violations%20by%20powerful%20States%2C%20the%20plunder%20of%20the%20commons%20by%20transnational%20corporations%2C%20the%20depredations%20of%20finance%20capital%2C%20and%20the%20ever-lengthening%20shadow%20of%20ecological%20disaster.%20And%20yet%20one%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20but%20marvel%20at%20Chomsky%E2%80%99s%20response%20to%20a%20question%20that%20Al%20Jazeera%20asked%20him%20in%20April%20this%20year%20in%20course%20of%20an%20interview.%20Here%E2%80%99s%20a%20look%20at%20that%20tete-a%E2%80%99-tete%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAJ%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3EFew%20intellectuals%20have%20caused%20greater%20controversy%20than%20yourself.%20Do%20you%20have%20any%20regrets%20for%20any%20of%20the%20positions%20that%20you%20have%20taken%20or%20not%20taken%20related%20to%20your%20advocacy%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENC%3Ci%3E%3A%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20having%20not%20taken%2C%20yes.%20I%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20retract%20those%20I%20have%20taken%2C%20but%20there%20are%20many%20things%20I%20should%20have%20done%20that%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20do%E2%80%A6..%20I%20became%20quite%20active%20in%20opposing%20the%20(Vietnam)%20war%20in%20the%20early%201960s%E2%80%A6%20but%20that%20was%20too%20late.%20Should%20have%20been%2010%20years%20earlier%20when%20the%20US%20began%20to%20support%20the%20French%20effort%20to%20reconquer%20their%20former%20colony%20and%2C%20when%20the%20French%20failed%2C%20the%20US%20took%20over%2C%20undermined%20the%20Geneva%20Accords%2C%20established%20a%20client%20state%20in%20the%20south%20that%20killed%2060%20or%2070%20thousand%20people.%20That%E2%80%99s%20when%20protest%20should%20have%20begun.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EUntil%20the%20latter%20part%20of%20the%201960s%2C%20there%20was%20no%20really%20organised%20opposition.%20That%20was%20criminal%20and%20I%20should%20have%20started%20earlier%2C%20same%20on%20other%20things%E2%80%A6.Take%20Israel%2C%20the%20leading%20issue%20of%20my%20life%20since%20early%20childhood.%20I%20started%20talking%20about%20the%20criminal%20nature%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20actions%20in%201969%20%E2%80%93%20it%20should%20have%20been%20much%20earlier.%20I%20was%20familiar%20with%20the%20repression%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20population%20in%20Israel.%20I%E2%80%99d%20seen%20it%20at%20first%20hand%E2%80%A6.%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20become%20involved%20until%20after%20the%20%E2%80%9967%20war%20and%20Israel%20initiated%20its%20policies%20of%20settlement%20and%20development%20in%20the%20occupied%20territories%2C%20which%20expanded%20and%20led%20to%20the%20current%20situation.%20I%20was%20much%20too%20mild%20in%20my%20criticism%20and%20much%20too%20late.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C(T)here%20are%20many%20things%20I%20should%20have%20done%20that%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20do%E2%80%9D.%20Nobler%20words%20than%20these%20have%20seldom%20been%20heard%20in%20our%20time.%20One%20hopes%20Noam%20Chomsky%C2%A0%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98the%20greatest%20living%20challenger%20of%20unjust%20power%20and%20delusions%E2%80%99%2C%20in%20Edward%20Said%E2%80%99s%20memorable%20words%20%E2%80%93continues%20to%20work%20and%20teach%20us%20all%20for%20many%20more%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EAnjan%20Basu%20can%20be%20reached%20at%20basuanjan52%40gmail.com.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701914400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F06%2F27102320%2Fnoam-chomsky.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fnoam-chomsky-at-95-challenger-unjust