%20selection%20committee%20for%20the%20national%20award%2C%20named%20in%20honour%20of%20the%20late%20Kannada%20poet%20Kuvempu%2C%20was%20headed%20by%20B.L.%20Shankar%2C%20president%20of%20the%20Rashtrakavi%20Kuvempu%20Trust.%20%C2%A0Nirmal%20Kanti%20Bhattacharya%2C%20Geetha%20Vijayakumar%20and%20Agrahara%20Krishnamurthy%20were%20members%20of%20the%20selection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20award%20includes%20a%20cash%20prize%20of%20Rs%205%20lakh%2C%20a%20silver%20medal%2C%20and%20a%20citation.%20The%20Rashtrakavi%20Kuvempu%20Trust%20instituted%20this%20national%20annual%20literary%20award%20in%202013%20to%20recognise%20litterateurs%20who%20had%20contributed%20to%20any%20language%20recognised%20by%20the%20constitution%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20the%20award%20was%20given%20to%20Tamil%20writer%20Imayam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20presentation%20ceremony%20for%20the%20award%20is%20scheduled%20for%20December%2029%2C%20Kuvempu%E2%80%99s%20birth%20anniversary%2C%20according%20to%20a%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMukhyopapadhyaya%20was%20born%20on%20November%202%2C%201935%2C%20in%20Mymensingh%20in%20present-day%20Bangladesh.%20His%3Cbr%3E%5Cnfamily%20migrated%20to%20Kolkata%20during%20the%20partition%20of%20India%2C%20when%20he%20was%20a%2012-year-old%20boy%20then.%20He%20started%20his%20career%20as%20a%20schoolteacher%20and%20also%20worked%20as%20a%20journalist%2C%20working%20for%20a%20Bengali%20newspaper%20called%20%3Cem%3EDesh%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20still%20with%20the%20%3Cem%3EAnand%20Bazar%3C%2Fem%3E%20newspaper.%20Mukhyopapadhyaya%E2%80%99s%20first%20story%20was%20published%20in%201959.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701876058000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F06204701%2Fmukh.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fthe-arts%2Fbengali-writer-shirshendhu-mukyopadhyaya-2023-kuvempu-award%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20writer%20brought%20%26quot%3Bnew%20sensibilities%20to%20hi